      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes sense that you feel this way, because your identity is tied to your past achievements, and the current reality feels like a cruel erasure of who you were. The shame you feel is a natural response to losing everything you worked for, but it does not define your worth as a human being. There is no way to \"wipe the slate clean\" because the past is gone, but you can choose to stop letting this single failure define your entire future.",
      "source": "target",
